  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      For the replacement of the sternum, there is no consensus regarding the most appropriate and
      most effective physiologically material. The use of ceramic implant offers significant
      operational time saving and biocompatibility coupled with the strength of the material allow
      us to realize a more natural operation, limiting the risk of infection and rejection.

      Main objective: to evaluate the efficiency of the replacement of the sternum by a ceramic
      implant on the respiratory capacity at 3 months post surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
